Reasoning: 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is the most likely category as the paper deals with algorithms for computing algebraic power series, which involves symbolic manipulation of mathematical expressions. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the complexity of algorithms for computing the Nth term of an algebraic series. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible category as the paper analyzes the arithmetic complexity of the algorithms. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper uses a classical theorem to prove the algebraicity of formal power series over finite fields. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is also a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with the computation of coefficients of algebraic power series.
